President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 11, 2012, as Military Spouse Appreciation Day. The proclamation recognizes the important role that military spouses play in supporting our Armed Forces and keeping the country safe. It acknowledges the sacrifices they make and the contributions they make to their communities. The proclamation highlights the efforts of the First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden in launching the Joining Forces initiative, which encourages Americans to recognize, honor, and serve military families. It also calls upon the people of the United States to honor military spouses with appropriate ceremonies and activities.